<p><i><a href="#top">Back to top</a></i></p>
<p><strong><a name="fileformatresume" id="fileformatresume"></a>What file format do the resumes need to be submitted in?</strong></p>
<p>The resumes will be submitted in the same file as the Proposal Narrative as a word processing file. Submit the entire package as a Microsoft Word or WordPerfect file.</p>
<p><i><a href="#top">Back to top</a></i></p>
<p><strong><a name="redasterisks" id="redasterisks"></a>Several online RFP forms have red asterisks next to various items. What do the red asterisks indicate?</strong></p>
<p>The red asterisks denote questions that are required for all applicants. LSC Grants will not allow users to submit the application until all required questions have been answered.</p>
<p><i><a href="#top">Back to top</a></i></p>
<p><strong><a name="topicsaddressedelsewhere" id="topicsaddressedelsewhere"></a> The following notation appears in the 2011 RFP at Performance Area One Criterion 3 and Performance Area 4 Criterion 8:</strong></p>
<div></div>
<p><i>Note to applicants: RFP topics for this criterion are addressed elsewhere and are not repeated here.</i></p>
<p><strong> How should applicants respond to these RFP criteria?</strong></p>
<p>Do not write anything for those criteria that read “Note to applicants: RFP topics for this criterion are addressed elsewhere and are not repeated here.”  Simply leave this section blank.</p>
<p><i><a href="#top">Back to top</a></i></p>
